						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken's one built into the front wall of the house of Siddappa Kōṭi.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Chaitra śu. 10</hi> of (probably) the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vikrama.</hi> It seems to state that in <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1]566, Dhātu,</hi> the <hi rend="bold">Dēśāyi</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Dēvagiri</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Karajige</hi> made a gift to god <hi rend="bold">Chenna-Basavēśvaradēva</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kukanūr.</hi> The latter date is wrong because the cyclic and the Śaka years given do not tally. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
